Yang Haodong gave speeches on the spirit of the 19th CPC Central Committee's 6th Plenary Session and Provincial Party Committee Conference at Malan Mountain.
Draw strength from the Party's Hundred Years' Struggle History.
According to the unified arrangements of the Provincial Party Committee,Yang Haodong, member of the Provincial Party Committee and director of the Provincial Party Committee Publicity Department, gave an interactive speech at the Molan Mountain Video Culture Park on the morning of December 10 to deepen the study and implementation of the spirit of the Sixth Plenary Session of the 19th CPC Central Committee, the important speech and instructions of General Secretary Xi Jinping to Hunan, and the spirit of the 12th Provincial Party Congress.
Yang Haodong combined his own understanding, personal experience, and in-depth yet comprehensive and systematic elucidation from three aspects, namely ideal belief and original mission, self revolution and youth party, and the Party's leaders and theories, to explain the core essence and practical demands of the All-members' Meeting.
He pointed out that we should learn and integrate the spirit of the conference and the important speeches and instructions of General Secretary Xi Jinping on Hunan, enhance the consciousness of thought, political awareness, and initiative to firmly safeguard the "two establishment" and achieve the "two maintenance", and unswervingly move forward in the direction pointed out by General Secretary Xi Jinping.
At the interactive exchange section, representatives from the grassroots cadres, enterprises and youth raised questions such as the relationship between the three historic resolutions, how to understand the determinative significance of "two establishments", how cultural enterprises grasp the guidance, and how the youth in the new era can draw strength from the party's hundred-year history. Yang Haodong answered each one of them in plain language and vivid examples. He earnestly sent greetings to the youth party members, exhorting them to draw strength from the Hundred Years of Struggle of the Party, to unite closely around the CPC Central Committee, and to stay with the Party unswervingly and use their youth to write responsibility and dedication.
